'''Carl Anders Theodor Starfelt''' (born 1 June 1995) is a Swedish professional [[association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[centre-back]] for [[La Liga]] club [[RC Celta de Vigo|Celta de Vigo]] and the [[Sweden men's national football team|Sweden national team]].

==Club career==
=== IF Brommapojkarna ===
Born in [[Stockholm]], Sweden, Starfelt began his career with [[IF Brommapojkarna]]. He made his senior debut on 9 March 2014, coming on as a substitute for [[Jacob Une]] in a [[Svenska Cupen]] match against [[Jönköpings Södra IF]] that ended in a goalless draw. He later made his [[Allsvenskan]] debut on 30 March 2014 against [[Kalmar FF]].<ref>{{Cite web|date=31 January 2019|title=Nya Blåvitts spelarporträtt: Carl Starfelt|url=https://www.nyablavitt.se/nya-blavitts-spelarportratt-carl-starfelt/|access-date=30 September 2020|language=sv-SE}}</ref>

=== IFK Göteborg ===
In January 2018, Starfelt joined [[IFK Göteborg]], one of the most successful clubs in Sweden. The transfer had been anticipated since 10 August 2017.<ref>{{cite web|date=10 August 2017 |lang=sv |title=Lämnar superettan – klar för IFK Göteborg |url=https://www.expressen.se/gt/sport/lamnar-superettan-klar-for-ifk-goteborg/ |website=www.expressen.se}}<!-- auto-translated from French by Module:CS1 translator --></ref>

He made his debut for the club on 17 February 2018, starting in a [[Svenska Cupen]] match against [[Varbergs BoIS]]. IFK Göteborg won the match 1–0.

=== Rubin Kazan ===
On 13 July 2019, he signed a four-year contract with [[Russian Premier League]] club [[FC Rubin Kazan]].<ref>{{cite web|publisher=[[FC Rubin Kazan]]|url=https://rubin-kazan.ru/posts/rubin-podpisal-kontrakt-s-karlom-starfeltom|title="РУБИН" ПОДПИСАЛ КОНТРАКТ С КАРЛОМ СТАРФЕЛЬТОМ|trans-title=Rubin signed a contract with Carl Starfelt|date=13 July 2019|language=Russian|access-date=19 July 2019|archive-date=19 October 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201019060251/https://rubin-kazan.ru/posts/rubin-podpisal-kontrakt-s-karlom-starfeltom|url-status=dead}}</ref>

=== Celtic ===
On 21 July 2021, Starfelt agreed on a four-year contract with [[Scottish Premiership]] side [[Celtic F.C.|Celtic]].<ref>{{cite web |last1=Mair |first1=Steven |title=Defender Carl Starfelt signs for Celtic from Rubin Kazan |url=https://www.dailyrecord.co.uk/sport/football/football-transfer-news/carl-starfelt-signs-celtic-ange-24560409 |website=Daily Record |access-date=21 July 2021 |language=en |date=21 July 2021 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210721174046/https://www.dailyrecord.co.uk/sport/football/football-transfer-news/carl-starfelt-signs-celtic-ange-24560409 |archive-date=21 July 2021 |url-status=dead }}</ref><ref>{{cite web|publisher=[[Celtic F.C.|Celtic]]|url=https://www.celticfc.com/news/2021/july/Celtic-delighted-to-welcome-Swedish-defender-Carl-Starfelt/|title=Celtic delighted to welcome Swedish defender Carl Starfelt|date=21 July 2021}}</ref> He would be involved in a [[centerback|centre-back]] partnership with fellow summer signing [[Cameron Carter-Vickers]] which helped Celtic win the [[2021–22 Scottish Premiership]] title, as they finished with the best defensive record in the league that season.<ref>{{Cite web |title=2021/22 Premiership {{!}} SPFL Archive |url=https://spfl.co.uk/league/premiership/archive/356 |access-date=31 December 2022 |website=spfl.co.uk}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |title=Premiership Goals Conceded {{!}} FootyStats |url=https://footystats.org/scotland/premiership/goals-conceded-table |access-date=31 December 2022 |website=footystats.org |language=en}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |last=Galindo |first=Alan |date=28 December 2022 |title=Carl Starfelt hails Cameron Carter-Vickers as he makes Celtic clean sheet demand |url=https://www.glasgowlive.co.uk/sport/carl-starfelt-hails-very-strong-25846466 |access-date=31 December 2022 |website=GlasgowLive |language=en}}</ref>

On 2 December 2021, Starfelt was given his first ever man of the match award for his performance in a 1–0 home win against [[Heart of Midlothian F.C.|Heart of Midlothian]] in the Scottish Premiership.<ref>{{Cite web |date=3 December 2021 |title=Carl Starfelt delighted with his first ever Man of the Match award won against Hearts |url=https://thecelticstar.com/carl-starfelt-delighted-with-his-first-ever-man-of-the-match-award-won-against-hearts/ |access-date=31 December 2022 |website=thecelticstar.com |language=en-GB}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |title=Celtic 1-0 Hearts: Kyogo Furuhashi's first-half goal sees Celtic edge past Hearts |url=https://www.skysports.com/football/news/11781/12483307/celtic-1-0-hearts-kyogo-furuhashis-first-half-goal-sees-celtic-edge-past-hearts |access-date=31 December 2022 |website=Sky Sports |language=en}}</ref>

On 19 December 2021, Starfelt started for Celtic against [[Hibernian F.C.|Hibernian]] in the [[2021–22 Scottish League Cup]] final. Celtic won 2–1, thanks to a brace from [[Kyogo Furuhashi]] and Starfelt collected his first career honour.<ref>{{Cite web |title=Premier Sports Cup (Sky Sports) |url=https://www.skysports.com/football/hibernian-vs-celtic/teams/460661?authId=1%2A1851zjz%2A_a%2AcmVHOXFFN1U0UC1xV0pLTGFqZXV2LWVwbWhUQVFQZnZycmhOWGpER3ozYWVSUk9zQU0yNV9sYTV4Tk5pb3oxUg.. |access-date=31 December 2022 |website=Sky Sports |language=en}}</ref>

On 18 April 2022, Starfelt scored an own goal against Rangers in extra time to give the latter a 2–1 win over Celtic, subsequently allowing Rangers to go on and win the Scottish Cup Final against Hearts.

On 14 August 2022, Starfelt scored his first goal for Celtic in a 5–0 win at [[Kilmarnock F.C.|Kilmarnock]] in the Scottish Premiership.<ref>{{cite web|publisher=[[Celtic FC]]|url=https://www.celticfc.com/news/2022/august/14/swede-feeling-for-carl-starfelt-after-his-first-goal/|title="Swede feeling for Carl Starfelt after his first goal"|date=14 August 2022}}</ref> His second goal for the club followed in a 9–0 win at [[Dundee United F.C.|Dundee United]] on 28 August 2022.<ref>{{cite web|publisher=[[Celtic FC]]|url=https://www.celticfc.com/news/2022/august/28/manager--we-got-our-rewards-for-hard-work-and-discipline/|title="Manager: We got our rewards for hard work and discipline"|date=28 August 2022}}</ref>

On 2 November 2022, Starfelt made his [[UEFA Champions League]] debut against [[Real Madrid CF|Real Madrid]] in a 5–1 defeat for Celtic at the [[Santiago Bernabéu Stadium|Santiago Bernabéu]].<ref>{{Cite web |last=UEFA.com |title=Real Madrid-Celtic {{!}} Line-ups |url=https://www.uefa.com/uefachampionsleague/match/2035731--real-madrid-vs-celtic/lineups/ |access-date=31 December 2022 |website=[[UEFA]] |language=en}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |title=Real Madrid 5-1 Celtic: Champions League holders thrash Scottish champions to qualify for last 16 as group winners |url=https://www.skysports.com/football/news/11787/12735022/real-madrid-5-1-celtic-champions-league-holders-thrash-scottish-champions-to-qualify-for-last-16-as-group-winners |access-date=31 December 2022 |website=Sky Sports |language=en}}</ref>

=== Celta Vigo ===
On 10 August 2023, Starfelt joined [[RC Celta de Vigo|Celta Vigo]] from Celtic for a reported fee of £4.3 million.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://rccelta.es/equipo/actualidad/carl-starfelt/|title=Carl Starfelt, contundencia, fiabilidad y solidez para fortalecer la defensa del RC Celta|publisher=[[Real Club Celta de Vigo|RC Celta]]|date=10 August 2023|access-date=10 August 2023|language=es}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|date=10 August 2023 |lang=en |title=Celtic: Carl Starfelt departure to Celta Vigo confirmed |url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/66461951 |website=www.bbc.com}}<!-- auto-translated from French by Module:CS1 translator --></ref>

He scored his first goal for the club on 4 November 2023, opening the scoring with a header from an [[Iago Aspas]] delivery in a 1–1 [[La Liga]] draw against [[Sevilla FC|Sevilla]].

Starfelt scored his second goal for Celta on 26 August 2024 in a La Liga match against [[Villarreal CF|Villarreal]]. Despite his goal, Celta were defeated 4–3.

==International career==
After having made two appearances for the [[Sweden men's national under-19 football team|Sweden U19]] team in 2014, Starfelt was called up to the [[Sweden men's national football team|Sweden national team]] for the first time on 30 September 2020 ahead of their games against [[Russia national football team|Russia]], [[Croatia national football team|Croatia]], and [[Portugal national football team|Portugal]] in October 2020.<ref>{{Cite web|title=Starfelt en av skrällarna i Blågult-truppen: "Har drömt om det sedan jag var liten"|url=https://www.fotbollskanalen.se/landslag/starfelt-en-av-skrallarna-i-blagult-truppen-har-dromt-om-det-sedan-jag-var-lit/|access-date=30 September 2020|website=fotbollskanalen|language=sv}}</ref> He made his full international debut on 8 October 2020 in a [[friendly game]] against Russia, playing all 90 minutes alongside [[Sebastian Holmén]] at [[centre-back]] in a 2–1 win for Sweden.<ref>{{Cite web|title=Svensk seger i Moskva|url=https://www.svenskfotboll.se/nyheter/landslag/2020/10/rus-swe/|access-date=9 October 2020|website=www.svenskfotboll.se|date=8 October 2020 |language=sv}}</ref>

On 12 May 2026, Starfelt was named in the Sweden squad for the [[2026 FIFA World Cup]].<ref>{{Cite web |date=2026-05-12 |title=Mystiskt inlägg efter petningen |url=https://www.expressen.se/sport/fotboll/landslaget/har-ar-sveriges-trupp-till-fotbolls-vm-2026/ |access-date=2026-05-15 |website=www.expressen.se |language=sv}}</ref>

== Personal life ==
Starfelt is in a relationship with Australian footballer [[Jacynta Galabadaarachchi]].<ref>{{Cite web |title=A namorada saiu para o Sporting, agora ele também quer deixar o Celtic |url=https://cnnportugal.iol.pt/jacynta-galabadaarachchi/carl-starfelt/a-namorada-saiu-para-o-sporting-agora-ele-tambem-quer-deixar-o-celtic |access-date=2025-05-13 |website=CNN Portugal |language=pt}}</ref>

